From 10f18c41185e8e26e93166cdbce3245543de51db Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Micheal Waltz <micheal@ecliptik.com>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 17:18:29 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] sdl3-dos: opt into SDL_HINT_DOS_PREFER_LFB for Mach64 perf
 (lever 1)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 9 lever 1 NXEngine-side companion to patches/SDL/0010 + 0011.

Sets SDL_HINT_DOS_PREFER_LFB="1" at OVERRIDE priority before SDL_Init,
identical shape to the existing SDL_HINT_DOS_ALLOW_DIRECT_FRAMEBUFFER
and SDL_HINT_DOS_MAX_BPP setters in the same #ifdef NXE_DOS block.

Effect: SDL3-DOS's LFB-vs-banked decision in DOSVESA_SetDisplayMode
flips from "prefer banked when usable" to "prefer LFB when available".
On the g2k Pentium OverDrive's Mach64 BIOS (M64VBE), this swaps the
~500 KB/s banked-window write path for a 5-10× faster LFB nearptr
copy through DPMI-mapped VRAM — the largest single perf lever in
the Phase 9 plan.

Why DOS needs this
------------------

DOS-only hint that targets the SDL3-DOS backend specifically. Has
no effect on non-DOS builds. Guarded by NXE_DOS to keep desktop
behaviour unchanged.

Layered with patches/SDL/0011 (lazy fb_state re-init) which is what
makes the hint actually engage LFB across mode-change boundaries.
Without 0011, the hint correctly flips the policy but fb_state stays
partial-stale after the second mode-set (Phase 8 attempt's failure
mode — see docs/PHASE8-FINDINGS.md).

See docs/PHASE9-15FPS-PLAN.md §3 Lever 1 for the full lever stack.
---
 src/main.cpp | 22 ++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 22 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/main.cpp b/src/main.cpp
index 0b7b828..a161313 100644
--- a/src/main.cpp
+++ b/src/main.cpp
@@ -379,6 +379,28 @@ int main(int argc, char *argv[])
   // 8bpp end-to-end is Phase 9 lever 3 work; needs palette management on
   // stage transitions. Tracked in docs/PHASE8-FINDINGS.md.
   SDL_SetHintWithPriority(SDL_HINT_DOS_MAX_BPP, "16", SDL_HINT_OVERRIDE);
+
+  // Patch 0045 (Phase 9 lever 1, 2026-04-26): prefer LFB over banked at the
+  // SDL3-DOS LFB-vs-banked decision (vendor/SDL/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c).
+  // Default DOS-backend policy prefers banked when both are usable, which is
+  // correct on the cards SDL3-DOS PR #15377 was developed against. On the
+  // g2k Pentium OverDrive's ATI Mach64 with M64VBE, banked-mode VESA writes
+  // through the 0xA0000 window are bandwidth-bound at ~500 KB/s effective;
+  // LFB through DPMI-mapped VRAM is 5-10× faster. The new hint
+  // SDL_HINT_DOS_PREFER_LFB (added by patches/SDL/0010) flips the policy.
+  //
+  // PREFER_LFB takes precedence over the existing
+  // SDL_HINT_DOS_ALLOW_DIRECT_FRAMEBUFFER hint in the LFB-vs-banked decision
+  // — we keep both set so the fast-path init's side-effect on fb_state
+  // population (the original reason patch 0032 set ALLOW_DIRECT_FRAMEBUFFER)
+  // remains active alongside the LFB preference.
+  //
+  // The lazy-fb_state-init lifecycle fix in patches/SDL/0011 is what makes
+  // this hint actually engage LFB across the engine's mode-change boundaries.
+  // Without 0011, this hint flipped the policy but fb_state stayed zero on
+  // the LFB code path (the wave-1 / Phase 8 attempt's failure mode).
+  // See docs/PHASE9-15FPS-PLAN.md §3 Lever 1 and docs/PHASE8-FINDINGS.md.
+  SDL_SetHintWithPriority(SDL_HINT_DOS_PREFER_LFB, "1", SDL_HINT_OVERRIDE);
 #endif
 
   // SDL3: SDL_Init returns bool (true on success); old `< 0` check would always be false.
-- 
